data.value: Stanley Bridge is a prominent architectural landmark in Alexandria, inaugurated in 2001 to alleviate traffic congestion along the Corniche. It stretches 400 meters and is 21 meters wide, with a design inspired by Italian architecture, particularly resembling the royal aesthetic of the Montaza Palace. The bridge is illuminated at night, offering a picturesque view of the Mediterranean Sea, and it has become a popular spot for tourists and locals alike.
